    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect PTI validation in deactivate EPS bearer context request handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `esm_recv_deactivate_eps_bearer_context_request` function was incorrectly rejecting network-initiated deactivate requests with unassigned PTI values. This caused unexpected behavior when processing valid deactivate requests from the network.\n\nThe issue was in the PTI validation logic where the function would flag unassigned PTI values as errors, unlike similar network-initiated procedures which accept them.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/SAP/esm_recv.c`: Modified PTI validation in `esm_recv_deactivate_eps_bearer_context_request` to allow unassigned PTI values, making it consistent with other network-initiated ESM procedures.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Send a deactivate EPS bearer context request message with PTI set to unassigned (0)\n2. Observe that the function returns `ESM_CAUSE_PTI_MISMATCH` instead of processing the request\n3. After the fix, the same request should be processed correctly, allowing the EPS bearer context deactivation to proceed\n\nThis fix ensures that network-initiated deactivate requests with unassigned PTI values are handled properly, resolving the unexpected behavior reported when calling `esm_recv_deactivate_eps_bearer_context_request()`.\n"
}